document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Grades 6-8 Physical Education

1CD64FE5E0FF4BD998518B56A7086684.description:
Demonstrates respect for self and others by asking for help and helping others
in various physical activities and games.

90A4BD4954384CD4A1753A2BDD16B345.description:
Identifies and participates in an enjoyable activity that prompts individual
self-expression.

502F3C7F3BC14ED18A29C4F7670E2ABC.description: Discusses how enjoyment can be increased in self-selected physical activities.

CEB229B25156491AB991845F3E045BEF.description: Applies strategies to overcome individual challenges in physical activity.

CB994096B0BB421B9B9AE458687E8987.description:
Identifies the five components of health-related fitness, and explains the
connections of being healthy (physically and mentally) and fit.

347AF6CDC48047C69290281B9D695547.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for
health, enjoyment, challenge, self expression, and/or social interaction.

AFBCFB57CB034113B3A178B43E123800.description:
Identifies specific safety concerns associated with physical activity and fitness
equipment.

AB05A9C4893B42ADB7D6CC7C6462A3EF.description:
Demonstrates cooperation skills and strategies that promote team or group
dynamics.

48190BFBCAF84A62A81AD5ED2193D025.description: Provides encouragement and feedback to peers without prompting

CC5F2D62769749DAA7DC56E585EDFFC4.description:
Applies rules and etiquette for physical activities and games, and creates dance
or rhythmic routines within a given set of parameters.

26CC9666823A41AF8D567AF39B2D3936.description:
Accepts responsibility for improving one’s own level of physical activity and
fitness.

5111B3AEB49946C68F3186F6B7124F5B.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

55F8EFF341E644908C6BA380BADD9A9F.description:
Maintains and reflects on a personal physical activity and nutrition log to
document learning and set goals for improvement.

28B89AE04E0B4596860C830EF19E4CDF.description:
Uses a SMART (specific, measurable, attainable, realistic, and timely) goal to
improve or maintain three areas of health-related fitness based on a fitness assessment.

A32D7E2117AE4A0FBB9ED2B44448EB64.description:
Develops strategies for balancing healthy food, snacks, and water intake
specific to daily physical activity.

DBC42286982B4B6198F05102CFDAD45B.description:
Explains how respiratory, muscular, and skeletal systems interact with each
other during physical activity.

16CE135FCA7349B2AC45E0049F814C01.description: Participates in a variety of self-selected fitness activities outside of school.

160868406DCD4C7EA6AAF112CCDF3E99.description:
Designs and implements a warm-up or cool-down for a self-selected physical
activity.

2B4D8858601645B5AD7B334BE7BE5C4C.description:
Designs a personal workout using the FITT principle (frequency, intensity, time,
type).

66D02371133E4527947917EC6491A845.description:
Calculates target heart rate zone and adjusts intensity during physical activity to
stay in the zone.

A04D2BD1646443FAA9AFF59F926A8D93.description:
Uses a variety of appropriate static and dynamic stretching techniques for
different muscle groups and understands when to apply them in their routine (i.e.
dynamic prior to activity and static post-activity).

4605475129F14311B04AAC4C5A8CAC64.description:
Describes the impact of cardiorespiratory endurance, muscular endurance, and
muscular strength on body composition.

8089D1C4A319470885A750DF2B82E634.description:
Explains health-related and skill-related components of fitness for self-selected
physical activities.

5BE03E07CBD1489BB486F4B128D26FF6.description:
Participates in physical activity three times a week outside of physical education
class.

2CFCC67213EF4E7092EDCB0D29CB8306.description:
Explains connections between physical activity and overall physical and mental
health.

44E75D9BF62048028F31ABBF07A90B38.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to
achieve and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

141E15510E9541819FAC730947274924.description:
Demonstrates a variety of shots to end a rally by using placement, force, or
timing.

DB1F3AF596B9442BA55300DC4393DD0D.description: Tactics and Shots, Net and Wall Games

AAFA6E11314B4DD590005FDEC011D0A0.description:
Demonstrates creating open space by varying force and direction, and forcing
the opponent to move from side to side and/or forward and backward.

93144D2EF71F46A09D36060053625AF0.description: Creating Space, Net and Wall Games

11332428EF434653B7201F9F5E7935DA.description:
Demonstrates the transitions from offense to defense and defense to offense
by recovering quickly, communicating with teammates, and capitalizing on an
advantage.

55470FFE0D27413EAECD6B425AA8C357.description:
Reduces open space during a small-sided game by working with teammates to
maximize coverage. (field and strike games)

5DD45E4FD69F4413B744390DDA336F9A.description:
Applies ways to reduce open space by staying on the goal side of the offensive
player and anticipate the speed of the object or person for the purpose of interception
or deflection. (invasion games)

6E79378402D34BB3972A26B472AC5A4C.description:
Performs a variety of shots to open space in a small-sided game. (field and
strike games)

CCAE3A842813465F94F886F9992B47E7.description:
Applies multiple ways to create open space (such as moving to open space
without a ball or object; using a variety of passes, pivots, and fakes; using the give and
go maneuver; using the width and length of the field/court; staying spread out on
offense; cutting and passing quickly; using fakes off the ball). (invasion games)

FF41F7F966084155B08D42E2D9D2D86E.description: Implements safety protocols in self-selected outdoor pursuits.

B28E8501B0A14E768DADAEA39905FC5D.description: Applies Newton's law of motion to various movement activities.

929BB8D52F8D4A3E8E169B553F9F7C75.description:
Demonstrates the concept of changing the speed, force, and trajectory of a
shot based on location of the object in relation to the target.

0B3A8DEA68454560A5466F1D622BB06F.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies, and tactics related to movement and performance.

BC3A083A61134FD88B42DBFBE792E719.description:
Performs the defensive position and slides in all directions without crossing the
feet in a small-sided game.

6BBDB29F0EF44BF4AEC96D0A3A61AC3F.description:
Performs two different movements with the ball or object (such as dribbling) to
create open space during a small-sided game.

2035CAAD45264922870F4F72344AFCD5.description:
Performs two different movements without the ball or object (such as the pivot,
give and go, fakes, or jab steps).

F52BAD800B6C4866810DF0C6BDD95232.description:
Performs controlled forehand and backhand volleys with competency with a
short- or long-handled implement during a small-sided game.

DB073A67464E458488DA9D16FD8F8E52.description:
Performs an underhand or overhand serve with competency, control, and weight
transfer in a small-sided game.

B429D9DDE79D4FF9AA33A0642958BAAB.description:
Performs shooting on goal with competency and accuracy during a small-sided
game.

AF701E12D67E4D8883FC2418988D9E4F.description:
Performs forehand and backhand strokes with competency while transferring
weight with correct timing, using a short- or long-handled implement during a small- sided
game.

C8F070B1456140DA9752E0CC54DE0322.description:
Performs striking a moving object for power, with competency, using an
implement in small-sided game play.

8E12AB6F8DC54CE29F54B27EC388022D.description:
Performs striking a stationary object for accuracy and power, using an implement,
with competency in activities (such as golf, hockey).

2DF1D9193C8C405A88043D6A331FDB79.description: Performs striking with competency in small-sided game play.

17F730B4393C40E2BFE296B0219DD8B1.description:
Performs dribbling skills with dominant and nondominant hand, foot, and
implements with control while moving, changing directions, and speed in small-sided
game play.

44704C0D19BC4E2FA5BBDA1500C622DB.description:
Performs a lead pass with competency, while moving or stationary, to a moving
receiver during small-sided game play.

583557FB9CEA4307AAF2AACD093E7F01.description:
Performs passing and receiving with hands, feet, or implements with competency
while moving, changing direction, speed, or level in small-sided game play.

FA62DCAC4A00437AB418D6E73AC8FF67.description:
Performs a mature catching pattern with hands (such as a ball or Frisbee) or an
implement (such as a lacrosse stick) in a dynamic environment or small-sided game play.

1F47D29690E34341B86F16416BB11A63.description:
Performs a mature throwing (underhand and overhand) pattern for distance,
control, and accuracy during small-sided and target game play.

BB729B3F7BCF4ED6BFCD28762DA5009C.description:
Exhibits command of rhythm and timing by creating a movement/rhythm
sequence to music as an individual or in a group.

C2E28B8D73D34989B8C9D7261843AE64.description: Performs correct technique for a variety of skills in two selected outdoor activities.

4267E400103B446ABEF39FB1A9180FD3.description:
Performs correct technique for a variety of skills in two selected individual
performance activities.

B5D30984E85F4215B0E20EB514445E32.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of
motor skills and movement patterns.
